android-sdk-installer (1.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Update build-tools to r23.0.1 to support newer Android Support library
    which requires 23+ version of build-tools to build apps correctly for
    pre-Android Lollipop devices.
    Note: Don't use latest which required JDK 8.
  * Update platform-tools to latest version: 25.0.3
  * Update tools to latest versoin: 25.2.4
  * Add dependency on JRE and JDK

 -- Chris Hubbard <chris_hubbard@sil.org>  Mon, 19 Dec 2016 14:57:18 -0500

android-sdk-installer (1.0.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add 64-bit package
  * Conditional dependencies based on distribution
  * Support updates
  * Delete downloaded zipfiles
  * Only support certain versions
    - The installer includes the list of urls that should be downloaded.
      It is also checked in and accessible via bitly links (see README.md).
      This is a way to make sure that a minimum version of the tools is
      available for the app-builders.  If the files are downloaded, then
      they have to match the expectations of the installer.

 -- Chris Hubbard <chris_hubbard@sil.org>  Tue, 30 Jun 2015 10:48:31 -0400

